		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=1426"><span id=Scholar>Beleni</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br>29 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Beleni&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p> So the other day I was in Oasis with a mediocre group, one of those where we were doing alright because nothing bad happened to us, but people pretty much weren't paying attention to their roles, they all just wanted to jump on any passing orc and beat them down. There was no healer, we just had a ranger or two, but they weren't doing any healing at all. The enchanter was spending his time casting DD spells instead of controlling the mob, etc. <br> Anyway, I volunteered to be the puller and everything was going fine *even though the enchanter insisted the ranger should pull*. Well, we got on particularly hard orc warrior and he didn't want to stop hitting on me. Nobody healed me, half the people didn't even stop medding to join in until I was halfway down in hp. <br> To make a long story short, I died. Now, I didn't really mind so much, I don't want to make it seem like it was anybody else's fault, I'll just say that things didn't go smoothly ;)<br> Then, as I was running back to Oasis, the 'chanter started saying how I shouldn't have been the one pulling, as if this is the reason I died. I think his reasoning was that I was highest on the aggro list and since I didn't take abuse as well as the ranger, I shouldn't have been pulling. <br> I'm just wondering what others might think about this. I often take a lot of punishment from the mob because I sometimes am the one dishing out the most damage, or that's the reason I gathered. I know that healers often get the mob angry and take some damage, as well as mages with their powerful spells. Did the enchanter have a point and the ranger should have pulled, hence topping the orc's aggro list for the duration of the fight, or was it just a bad fight? I'm a little hesitant to offer to pull now because of this, even though I was under the impression that monks make some of the best pullers. </p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Beleni<br>Lowly Monk on Karana</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >4 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
